HEADWORD: Youngly
<hw>Young"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>geonglic</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Like a young person or thing; young; youthful.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Youngly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Youngly
<hw>Young"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a young manner;
in the period of youth; early in life.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ignorantly; weakly.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Young Men's Christian Association</ent>⟦br⟧
